This paper deals with off-policy policy evaluation in reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on importance sampling estimators and their variance in the context of finite horizon problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as these categories are closely related to the topic of the paper. The paper also touches on control systems (cs.SY) and neural networks (cs.NE), which are relevant but less central to the main topic.
